   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Remarks
</p>
      <p>
Pedroli-Christen (1993)
provisionally included 
<tp:taxon-name>
H. helveticum
</tp:taxon-name>
, 
<tp:taxon-name>
H. jurassicum
</tp:taxon-name>
and 
<tp:taxon-name>
H. cornigerum
</tp:taxon-name>
in her concept of 
<tp:taxon-name>
H. alemannicum
</tp:taxon-name>
and noted that this complex may constitute one polytypic species. We adopt this view but follow 
Spelda (2008)
in using the older name 
<tp:taxon-name>
helveticum
</tp:taxon-name>
.
</p>
